  "response": "To prevent pipes from freezing, it is generally recommended to keep the thermostat set to at least 55\u00b0F (12\u00b0C) when you're away from home or during extremely cold weather. This temperature helps maintain a warm enough environment to keep the pipes from freezing, which can cause them to burst and lead to significant water damage. However, the exact temperature can vary depending on factors such as the location of the pipes, insulation, and local climate conditions.",
